# NeuralGTO Frontend — Environment Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# USAGE:
#   Local dev:   copy to .env.local — Vite loads it automatically (gitignored)
#   Production:  set these as Environment Variables in the Cloudflare Pages
#                dashboard (Settings → Environment variables → Production)
#                DO NOT commit .env.local or .env.production to git.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Backend API base URL (no trailing slash).
#
# Dev:        Leave empty — Vite proxy rewrites /api → http://localhost:8000
# Production: Set to your Oracle Cloud backend URL, e.g.
#             https://api.neuralgto.com          (if using a custom domain)
#             https://neuralgto.your-domain.trycloudflare.com  (CF Tunnel)
#
# This value is baked into the compiled JS at build time by Vite.
# Changing it requires a new build + deploy.
VITE_API_URL=
